HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 526
By Hale
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Crystal Kennedy on
her selection as the 2024–2025 Cannon County
School District Supervisor of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those outstanding professionals who have devoted their careers to providing
the highest quality education for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Crystal Kennedy is one such estimable administrator, who has
distinguished herself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Kennedy has been selected as the 2024–2025 Cannon County School
District Supervisor of the Year, an honor most befitting her outstanding tenure as a Career and
Technical Education (CTE) director, as it recognizes the positive influence she has on so many
young lives; and
WHEREAS, with a career at the Cannon County School District (CCSD) spanning
eighteen years, Mrs. Kennedy is an extremely talented and compassionate administrator who
works assiduously to motivate her students, teachers, and staff to reach their full potential as
scholars, professionals, and citizens; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Kennedy began her teaching career at CCSD as a CTE teacher at
Cannon County High School (CCHS); she later assumed the director role, in which position she
piloted the CTE education initiative for students in grades six through eight and brought funding
to the district for CTE students; and
WHEREAS, during her tenure, Crystal Kennedy has been the recipient of various
awards, and she was instrumental in bringing innovative programs to CCHS, such as the HUB,
the Farm Lab, and the Cannon Paw Print Shop; and
